  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large clay or ceramic tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the lamb pieces and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped mitsuba, dum, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional chopped mitsuba if desired.",
    "Place the tagine on a slate tile vessel to serve.",
    "Let it rest for 10 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or over couscous."
  ],
